Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"umbraco-community/awesome-umbraco","categoryHTML":"<h2>Community</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://24days.in/umbraco-cms/\">24 Days In Umbraco</a> - yearly advent calendar for Umbraco content.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-17T18:58:32.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"umbraco-community/awesome-umbraco","categoryHTML":"<h2>Website utilities</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://our.umbraco.com/packages/backoffice-extensions/matryoshka-tabs-for-umbraco-8/\">Matryoshka</a> - Adding back tabs in Umbraco</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-17T18:53:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"umbraco-community/awesome-umbraco","categoryHTML":"<h2>Official</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://codegarden20.com/\">CodeGarden Conference</a></li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-17T18:49:47.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"umbraco-community/awesome-umbraco","categoryHTML":"<h2>Community</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://candidcontributions.com/\">Candid Contributions</a> - a fortnightly podcast discussing all things Umbraco and open source.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-17T18:49:47.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"umbraco-community/awesome-umbraco","categoryHTML":"<h2>Community</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/umbracocommunity/\">Official YouTube Channel</a> - the Umbraco community YouTube channel.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-17T18:49:47.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JoseDeFreitas/awesome-youtubers","categoryHTML":"<h2>Electronics and communication</h2>","itemHTML":"<h2>Electronics and communication</h2>\n<p>All tutorials and videos of every single old as well as new electronic components available in the market. How to get started with electronics stuff, every useful resource, and also get advice/recommendation which product to use and why from persons having much more experience in this field.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/ALLABOUTELECTRONICS\"><img align=\"left\" height=\"94px\" width=\"94px\" alt=\"Channel&#x27;s avatar\" src=\"https://yt3.ggpht.com/a/AATXAJy96DtZPu2EJwh5eXuSn6-ru4wz1C4xFTs8GBcwYA=s176-c-k-c0x00ffffff-no-rj\"></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/ALLABOUTELECTRONICS\"><strong>All About Electronics</strong></a> <br>\nContent about: Electronics and Communication <br>\nFeatured playlists: <code>BJT</code>, <code>Analog Electronics</code>, <code>Network Analysis</code>. <br>\n<br></p>\n<p><a href=\"#contents\">🔼 Back to the top</a></p>\n<details>\n\t<summary>Credits</summary>\n<p>The awesome-youtubers logo and the corresponding badges icons were made by <a href=\"https://github.com/JoseDeFreitas/\">José De Freitas</a>.</p>\n<p>The badges were created without following any design structure, though the <a href=\"https://github.com/JoseDeFreitas/awesome-youtubers/blob/main/media/logo.svg\">awesome-youtubers logo</a> is inspired by the <a href=\"https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome/blob/main/media/logo.svg\">awesome logo</a> and the <a href=\"https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome-nodejs/blob/master/media/logo.svg\">awesome-nodejs logo</a>. The two play icons were created following the play button of the <a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/z6Sl4j9zQ88oUKNy0G3PAMiVwy8DzQLh_ygyvBXv0zVNUZ_wQPN_n7EAR2By3dhoUpX7kTpaHjRPni1MHwKpaBJbpNqdEsHZsH4q\">YouTube logo</a>. It's just a representation, I'm not using the YouTube logo itself.</p>\n<p>The upvote and downvote icons located at the right-most part of every YouTuber's name line were taken from <a href=\"https://www.flaticon.com\">flaticon.com</a>; more specifically, they were made by the <a href=\"https://www.flaticon.com/authors/pixel-perfect\">Pixel Perfect</a> team (all credits of this icons to them. Thank you!). I modified them by changing just the color (green for upvote and red for downvote. Did this manually in the .svg files).</p>\n<p>The list style is heavily inspired by <a href=\"https://github.com/mhxion/awesome-discord-communities\">awesome-discord-communities</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/mhxion/awesome-discord-communities\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1002,\"repo\":\"mhxion/awesome-discord-communities\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->, created by <a href=\"https://github.com/mhxion\">mhxion</a>. This repository was my inspiration as I consider <a href=\"https://github.com/JoseDeFreitas/awesome-youtubers\">this list</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/JoseDeFreitas/awesome-youtubers\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">2.5k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":2529,\"repo\":\"JoseDeFreitas/awesome-youtubers\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> also looks good with the same table-style in this file, as well as the useful <a href=\"https://github.com/JoseDeFreitas/awesome-youtubers/blob/main/badges.md\">badges</a>.</p>\n</details>","updatedAt":"2020-10-17T18:48:04.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"EbookFoundation/free-programming-books","categoryHTML":"<h4>Open Source Ecosystem</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://do1.dr-chuck.net/net-intro/EN_us/net-intro.pdf\">Introduction to Networking</a> - Charles Severance (PDF)</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-17T17:28:06.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"h4cc/awesome-elixir","categoryHTML":"<h2>Testing</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/derekkraan/walkman\">Walkman</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/derekkraan/walkman\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">46</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":46,\"repo\":\"derekkraan/walkman\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Isolate tests from the real world, inspired by Ruby's VCR.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-17T17:22:33.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"h4cc/awesome-elixir","categoryHTML":"<h2>Date and Time</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/rengel-de/calixir\">calixir</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/rengel-de/calixir\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1,\"repo\":\"rengel-de/calixir\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Calixir is a port of the Lisp calendar software calendrica-4.0 to Elixir.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-17T17:21:25.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"EbookFoundation/free-programming-books","categoryHTML":"<h3>Graphics Programming</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.scratchapixel.com\">Learn Computer Graphics From Scratch!</a> - Scratchapixel (🚧 <em>in process</em>)</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-17T16:31:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"EbookFoundation/free-programming-books","categoryHTML":"<h3>Graphics Programming</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cs.csustan.edu/~rsc/CS3600F00/Notes.pdf\">Notes for a Computer Graphics Programming Course</a> - Dr. Steve Cunningham (PDF)</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-17T16:31:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"EbookFoundation/free-programming-books","categoryHTML":"<h3>Unix</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://homepages.uc.edu/~thomam/Intro_Unix_Text/TOC.html\">INTRODUCTION TO UNIX</a> - Mark A. Thomas</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-17T16:31:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Career</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/@rvprabhu/levels-of-abstraction-in-engineering-management-6bac9410e89a\">Levels of abstraction in engineering management</a> - Another take on the differences between Manager, Manager of Managers, Head of Org and Head of Function.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-17T15:57:34.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"iamericfletcher/awesome-r-learning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Topic Areas</h2><h3>Viz</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://extremepresentation.typepad.com/files/choosing-a-good-chart-09.pdf\">Chart Suggestions — A thought-starter on choosing the way to show your data</a> - Author: Andrew Abela, Ph.D.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-17T15:37:42.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Roles</h2><h3>Engineering Managers</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>“One of your roles is to act as an information filter in both directions” (<a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=19187593\">source</a>) - Some tips on how to balance which kind of information needs to be shared or muted.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-17T15:25:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Roles</h2><h3>Engineering Managers</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=24802483\">A vitally important part of the job: being a crap shield</a> - “A lot of the work of an EM is wading into the slurry pit with a shovel so your team are free to get the job done”.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-17T15:25:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Engineering</h2><h3>The Technical Engineering Manager</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://increment.com/teams/do-engineering-managers-need-to-be-technical/\">Do engineering managers need to be technical?</a> - Yes. “Looking forward to the next 30 years of management trends, only a few things seem certain: Managers should be technical, and the definition of technical will continue to change.”</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-17T15:25:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Engineering</h2><h3>The Technical Engineering Manager</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>“The best managers I met tended to be those that if the circumstance required it, could do the job of those two levels below.” (<a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=23891984\">source</a>) - Another way of putting it: managers needs domain knowledge and to know the work their reports do.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-17T15:25:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Engineering</h2><h3>The Technical Engineering Manager</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>“Over the years we have developed the policy that it is important for the supervisor to thoroughly know and understand the work of his group.” (<a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=20683609\">source</a>) - This quote is <a href=\"https://amzn.com/0060845791/?tag=kevideld-20\">from David Packard</a> (HP co-founder), decades before current <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Management_fad\">management fad</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-17T15:25:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Career</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.wired.com/story/amazon-wants-to-win-at-games-so-why-hasnt-it/\">Amazon Wants to 'Win at Games.' So Why Hasn't It?</a> - “Any product manager can go between any business—from groceries to film to games to Kindle. The skillset is interchangeable. They just have to learn the particular market.”</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-17T15:25:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Health</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://supermemo.guru/wiki/Good_sleep,_good_learning,_good_life\">Good sleep, good learning, good life</a> - An e-book-sized synthesis on sleep research “with a view to practical applications, esp. in people who need top-quality sleep for their learning or creative achievements.”</li>","updatedAt":"2020-10-17T15:25:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"vuejs/awesome-vue","categoryHTML":"<h2>Components &#x26; Libraries</h2><h4>Component Collections</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/uiv-lib/uiv\">uiv</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/uiv-lib/uiv\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">885</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{